DIRECTIONS

B The Johns Hopkins University Columbia Center
From I-695: Take 1-70 west (exit 16) to U.S. 29. Take 29
south to Maryland 175 and travel east on 175 toward
Jessup. Turn right at Thunder Hill Road, then turn right
again at Twin Knolls Road. The Center is located at
5457 Twin Knolls Road.

From I-95: Take 175 toward Columbia to Thunder Hill
Road and turn left. Turn right at Twin Knolls Road. The
Center is located at 5457 Twin Knolls Road.

From I-495: Take 29 north (exit 30) to 175 east and turn
right at Thunder Hill Road. Turn right again at Twin Knolls
Road; the Center is located at 5457 Twin Knolls Road.

B Applied Physics Laboratory

From I-95: Exit at Maryland 32 west (exit 38) and travel to
U.S. 29 south. Travel on 29 approximately 3 miles to Johns
Hopkins Road. Turn right and APL will be on your right.

B School of Advanced International Studies (SAIS)

From I-695: Take Maryland 295 (Baltimore-Washington
Parkway ) south to the New York Avenue exit. Proceed
along New York and bear right onto Massachusetts
Avenue. SAIS is located at 1740 Massachusetts Avenue,
N.W, just beyond 17th Street.

From I-95: Take 1-495 east to Maryland 295, travel south
on 295, and follow directions above.

B Continuing Professional Programs, Aberdeen, Md.

From I-95: Exit at Maryland 22 (exit 85) and travel east
directly to Aberdeen Proving Ground. Ask the MP at the
gate for directions to Building 3147 on Raritan Road.

B Parkway Center

From Maryland 295 (Baltimore-Washington Parkway ),
southbound: Exit at Dorsey Road and turn left onto
Parkway Drive. Parkway Center will be on your left.

B Chesapeake Bay Institute in Shady Side, Md.
Call the Institute for directions at (301) 269-5373.
